14 the effective date of this act as follows:
15 (i) Two public members that represent charitable organizations
16 engaged in providing services to victims, dependents, and relatives of
17 victims. At least one such member shall represent charitable
18 organizations engaged in providing services to victims of sexual assault
19 as defined by section 28-319 or 28-320, human trafficking as defined by
20 section 28-830, or domestic abuse as defined by section 42-903;
21 (ii) Two public members that have training and relevant work
22 experience with victims, dependents, and relatives of victims. At least
23 one such member shall have training and relevant work experience with
24 victims of sexual assault as defined by section 28-319 or 28-320, human
25 trafficking as defined by section 28-830, or domestic abuse as defined by
26 section 42-903; and
27 (iii) One public member who is a victim.
28 (3) The members of the committee shall select a chairperson who is a
29 member of the commission.
